Based on the context and the comment referencing Mathlib PR #30112, the missing proof is a direct application of the theorem `ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.exists_map_volume_eq`, which establishes the existence of a kernel representation mapping the volume measure on the unit interval to the target kernel for standard Borel spaces.

```lean
namespace ArrayModel

open unitInterval

section Aux

-- from Mathlib PR #30112
theorem representation {α β : Type*} {mα : MeasurableSpace α} {mβ : MeasurableSpace β}
    [Nonempty β] [StandardBorelSpace β]
    (κ : Kernel α β) [IsMarkovKernel κ] :
    ∃ (f : α → I → β), Measurable (Function.uncurry f) ∧ ∀ a, volume.map (f a) = κ a :=
